      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 27
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 997.1 Carrera is a purist\u2019s specification, powered by a 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six mated to a crisp G97 6-speed manual transaxle. The mid-range torque is robust, and the engine exhibits no signs of bore scoring. Crucially, the IMS bearing has been proactively upgraded to a ceramic dual-row solution. The suspension retains its factory composure, utilizing MacPherson struts up front and a multi-link rear setup for precise turn-in and high-speed stability. Hydraulic steering feedback is communicative, and the braking system features four-piston monobloc calipers that offer firm, fade-resistant modulation. This is a mechanically sound driver\u2019s car ready for spirited canyon carving.",
